        <h2>Understanding Changes in the MGSU Revaluation Marksheet</h2>
        <p>When you view your Univindia Net MGSU Revaluation Result, you may encounter different outcomes. It is important to understand what each state means for your academic record:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Marks Increased (Positive Revaluation):</strong> If your marks have significantly improved, the university will issue a new digital marksheet. This updated score replaces your old one and is used for all future degree calculations.</li>
            <li><strong>No Change (NC):</strong> This indicates that after re-checking, the examiner found the original marks to be accurate. In this case, your initial result stands.</li>
            <li><strong>Marks Decreased:</strong> While rare, the revaluation process involves a full re-check, and if errors are found that inflated the original score, the marks can technically decrease. However, most students only see an "Increase" or "No Change" status.</li>
            <li><strong>Result Withheld (RW-REVAL):</strong> Sometimes, revaluation results for specific candidates are withheld due to technical discrepancies in the application form or fee payment. These are usually resolved within a few weeks.</li>
        </ul>

